      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk. i was just looking at the stars and thinking about how much effort we all put into everything. school, work, relationships... it all feels so stupid when you realize the universe is just gonna end in heat death anyway. like we're just tiny accidents playing games that won't matter in a billion years. does any of it actually mean anything to you? or is it all just a lie we tell ourselves to stay busy?",
